1
00:00:16,271 --> 00:00:17,378
Why didn't you move away?

2
00:00:17,378 --> 00:00:18,338
[Episode 4]

3
00:00:18,338 --> 00:00:20,970
Were you planning to go for it?

4
00:00:22,837 --> 00:00:24,837
For crying out loud.

5
00:00:24,837 --> 00:00:26,937
No matter how much you want it,

6
00:00:26,937 --> 00:00:30,537
there's an 18-year-old inside this body.

7
00:00:30,537 --> 00:00:32,237
It would have been a catastrophe
if I hadn't stopped.

8
00:00:32,237 --> 00:00:34,804
How irresponsible can you be?

9
00:00:36,271 --> 00:00:39,171
So this is how I would have felt.

10
00:00:39,970 --> 00:00:46,137
This is how it would've felt
if Yun Jae had leaned toward me.

11
00:00:46,137 --> 00:00:47,637
What?

12
00:00:47,637 --> 00:00:52,670
So you two never even got this far?

13
00:00:52,670 --> 00:00:54,237
No way.

14
00:00:55,171 --> 00:00:58,104
We did,

15
00:00:58,104 --> 00:00:59,837
but I didn't get to see it.

16
00:01:00,503 --> 00:01:05,637
I was asleep when it happened.

17
00:01:06,804 --> 00:01:09,171
I had pulled an all-nighter
for a school event,

18
00:01:09,171 --> 00:01:13,271
so I dozed off when Yun Jae
went to get me coffee.

19
00:01:40,438 --> 00:01:42,004
When it happened,

20
00:01:42,004 --> 00:01:44,004
I was so startled that I did wake up,

21
00:01:44,004 --> 00:01:45,770
but I couldn't open my eyes.

22
00:01:46,870 --> 00:01:49,137
I should have opened my eyes right away,

23
00:01:49,137 --> 00:01:50,338
but I lost the window of opportunity,

24
00:01:50,338 --> 00:01:52,904
and I didn't know anymore
when I could open my eyes.

25
00:01:52,904 --> 00:01:53,804
So?

26
00:01:53,804 --> 00:01:57,338
So I kept my eyes closed all the way home.

27
00:01:57,338 --> 00:02:01,670
Why couldn't I open my eyes then?

28
00:02:01,670 --> 00:02:02,937
If only I had,

29
00:02:02,937 --> 00:02:06,470
our relationship would have moved
forward at lightning speed.

30
00:02:07,603 --> 00:02:10,071
Don't be too sad.

31
00:02:10,071 --> 00:02:12,037
You might be mistaken.

32
00:02:12,037 --> 00:02:15,004
You tend to get the wrong idea easily.

33
00:02:15,004 --> 00:02:16,071
I was not mistaken.

34
00:02:16,071 --> 00:02:17,770
But you said you didn't see.

35
00:02:17,770 --> 00:02:20,837
How can you be sure it was
his lips that touched yours?

36
00:02:20,837 --> 00:02:24,670
How can anyone mistake that?

37
00:02:25,704 --> 00:02:27,537
Is she sleeping?

38
00:02:30,870 --> 00:02:32,537
Maybe this is what happened.

39
00:02:33,904 --> 00:02:37,237
It didn't feel like a quick pat like that.

40
00:02:37,237 --> 00:02:38,870
Then...

41
00:02:42,704 --> 00:02:45,737
She's drooling.

42
00:02:46,570 --> 00:02:48,104
Maybe this is what happened.

43
00:02:48,537 --> 00:02:53,503
It didn't feel like that either.

44
00:02:53,503 --> 00:02:56,137
But then again, I didn't see anything.

45
00:03:00,204 --> 00:03:01,737
This?

46
00:03:04,637 --> 00:03:06,271
Was it like this?

47
00:03:08,371 --> 00:03:10,304
Yeah.

48
00:03:13,037 --> 00:03:16,237
Huh?

49
00:03:16,237 --> 00:03:19,004
Huh?

50
00:03:20,004 --> 00:03:21,670
You jerk.

51
00:03:22,137 --> 00:03:23,537
You jerk!

52
00:03:24,137 --> 00:03:25,438
What?

53
00:03:25,438 --> 00:03:26,404
Why did you hit me?

54
00:03:26,404 --> 00:03:29,371
I was just trying to help because
you seemed so confused.

55
00:03:29,371 --> 00:03:32,071
You can't help me. You're a little kid.

56
00:03:32,071 --> 00:03:33,304
How dare you?

57
00:03:33,304 --> 00:03:35,137
Why would you help me? Huh?

58
00:03:35,603 --> 00:03:37,637
Stop. Stop. Stop.

59
00:03:37,637 --> 00:03:41,338
If you keep kicking me, I'll plant these
on whoever I see.

60
00:03:41,338 --> 00:03:42,704
They're not yours. They're Yun Jae's.

61
00:03:42,704 --> 00:03:43,637
Precisely.

62
00:03:43,637 --> 00:03:45,171
So why are you mad at me?

63
00:03:45,171 --> 00:03:47,904
It was your precious Yun Jae's lips
that landed on yours.

64
00:03:47,904 --> 00:03:50,137
Think of it as a rerun of a show you missed.

65
00:03:50,137 --> 00:03:52,770
You had your eyes wide open this time.
So you didn't miss a thing, right?

66
00:03:52,770 --> 00:03:54,338
Was it good? Was it?

67
00:03:54,338 --> 00:03:56,237
You're not Yun Jae. You're Kang Gyeong Jun.

68
00:03:56,237 --> 00:03:57,804
Since you know that,

69
00:03:57,804 --> 00:04:00,137
stop making me play Yun Jae again.

70
00:04:01,371 --> 00:04:04,837
I told you I'd rebel if you kept nagging me.

71
00:04:07,137 --> 00:04:08,071
Where are you going?

72
00:04:08,071 --> 00:04:09,171
Home.

73
00:04:09,171 --> 00:04:10,503
To Kang Gyeong Jun's home.

74
00:04:18,004 --> 00:04:20,404
So you didn't know Gyeong Jun was hurt.

75
00:04:21,104 --> 00:04:25,438
Didn't my sister tell you?

76
00:04:25,804 --> 00:04:27,237
Your sister?

77
00:04:27,237 --> 00:04:30,770
You were talking to my sister
at school earlier.

78
00:04:31,438 --> 00:04:34,770
Ms. Gil Da Ran is my sister.

79
00:04:35,503 --> 00:04:37,837
I suppose you also met my brother-in-law.

80
00:04:37,837 --> 00:04:39,304
Your brother-in-law?

81
00:04:42,304 --> 00:04:46,537
They're getting married next month.

82
00:04:49,271 --> 00:04:52,704
My brother-in-law's a doctor
at this hospital.

83
00:04:52,704 --> 00:04:56,470
He's a doctor at this hospital?

84
00:04:57,904 --> 00:05:00,004
You can go now.

85
00:05:04,204 --> 00:05:07,438
How do Da Ran and Yun Jae know her anyway?

86
00:05:08,071 --> 00:05:10,137
Why did they lie to me?

87
00:05:14,704 --> 00:05:15,970
What now?

88
00:05:15,970 --> 00:05:21,704
There's something I forgot
to give you earlier.

89
00:05:22,104 --> 00:05:24,804
Come in, Ms. Gil.

90
00:05:39,204 --> 00:05:42,438
Won't that give you indigestion?
It's so late at night.

91
00:05:42,438 --> 00:05:45,204
Plus, it's very high in calories.
It's probably not healthy.

92
00:05:45,937 --> 00:05:48,637
This dude's going to gain weight
and have an upset stomach.

93
00:05:49,137 --> 00:05:53,271
Make sure you eat slowly. And brush
your teeth once you're done eating.

94
00:05:53,271 --> 00:05:55,937
Just give me what you forgot
to give me earlier.

95
00:05:58,470 --> 00:06:00,237
You may not like this,

96
00:06:00,237 --> 00:06:02,870
but I think this is very important.

97
00:06:02,870 --> 00:06:03,804
What now?

98
00:06:03,804 --> 00:06:05,870
What do I have to do in Seo Yun Jae's stead?

99
00:06:06,737 --> 00:06:10,670
This is what you've missed
at school since the accident.

100
00:06:12,137 --> 00:06:14,338
You're a student.

101
00:06:14,338 --> 00:06:17,603
You can't go to school, but you should
still keep up with your studies.

102
00:06:17,603 --> 00:06:19,037
I'll help you.

103
00:06:19,037 --> 00:06:20,104
Whose class notes are these?

104
00:06:20,104 --> 00:06:23,537
The best student in your class.

105
00:06:23,537 --> 00:06:26,237
Once I return, this kid will
become second best.

106
00:06:26,237 --> 00:06:28,371
Why? Because I'll be the top student.

107
00:06:29,004 --> 00:06:31,837
I did hear you had done quite well
back in the States.

108
00:06:31,837 --> 00:06:34,438
Not just well. My grades were excellent.

109
00:06:34,438 --> 00:06:36,870
I was beyond compare.

110
00:06:37,470 --> 00:06:40,637
And if you want to keep that up,
you need to keep studying.

111
00:06:40,637 --> 00:06:42,670
I will. I'll go to Seoul National University.

112
00:06:42,670 --> 00:06:43,570
SNU?

113
00:06:43,570 --> 00:06:45,637
I could go to Harvard if I wanted to,

114
00:06:45,637 --> 00:06:49,104
but I promised mom I'd go to SNU.

115
00:06:52,670 --> 00:06:54,804
That's why mom bought me this house.

116
00:06:57,737 --> 00:06:58,537
I see.

117
00:06:58,537 --> 00:07:02,171
I bet your mom is very proud of you,
given your good grades

118
00:07:02,171 --> 00:07:04,137
and given how well you're doing for yourself.

119
00:07:06,904 --> 00:07:10,037
I'll help you go to SNU, okay?

120
00:07:10,037 --> 00:07:11,404
Really?

121
00:07:12,304 --> 00:07:15,670
Then help me with this for starters.

122
00:07:19,371 --> 00:07:21,037
It's math.

123
00:07:21,870 --> 00:07:24,537
I specialize in Korean history...

124
00:07:27,570 --> 00:07:29,737
This is integral calculus.

125
00:07:38,271 --> 00:07:40,870
Gyeong Jun's fine. There's nothing
for you to worry about,

126
00:07:40,870 --> 00:07:41,670
so go back home.

127
00:07:44,338 --> 00:07:48,470
I'll tell him to get in touch with you.

128
00:07:48,470 --> 00:07:50,037
He won't be able to call,
but I'm sure he'll text you.

129
00:07:55,037 --> 00:07:57,904
Gyeong Jun's in a coma.

130
00:07:57,904 --> 00:08:00,970
How would he have been able to text me?

131
00:08:25,171 --> 00:08:27,737
Gyeong Jun, I'm waiting for you
to get in touch with me.

132
00:08:27,737 --> 00:08:28,870
I want to know how you are.

133
00:08:28,870 --> 00:08:31,237
At least text me before I leave.

134
00:08:31,237 --> 00:08:33,304
She won't leave if I don't
text her, will she?

135
00:08:42,402 --> 00:08:43,603
[Take care. Bye]

136
00:08:43,603 --> 00:08:45,104
Take care.

137
00:08:46,603 --> 00:08:48,537
Bye?

138
00:08:52,537 --> 00:08:56,237
But she came all this way.
Was the message too succinct?

139
00:09:12,503 --> 00:09:14,637
Darn it.

140
00:09:16,470 --> 00:09:18,137
Where are you going?

141
00:09:18,870 --> 00:09:20,371
You're Gyeong Jun's uncle, right?

142
00:09:20,371 --> 00:09:21,470
Yes.

143
00:09:21,470 --> 00:09:23,804
Are you Gyeong Jun's friend from the States?

144
00:09:23,804 --> 00:09:25,804
Is is true what you told me over the phone?

145
00:09:25,804 --> 00:09:26,904
Yes.

146
00:09:26,904 --> 00:09:29,237
I'm going to take Gyeong Jun to the States.

147
00:09:37,870 --> 00:09:41,271
If she's that close a friend,
why don't you just tell her the truth?

148
00:09:41,271 --> 00:09:43,304
You don't know what Mary's like.

149
00:09:43,304 --> 00:09:45,104
I doubt she'd cause you trouble.

150
00:09:45,104 --> 00:09:47,071
Yes, she will.

151
00:09:47,071 --> 00:09:51,870
Gil Teacher, Mary will now
try to stay by my side.

152
00:09:54,137 --> 00:09:56,670
Gyeong Jun,

153
00:09:56,670 --> 00:09:59,338
I'll be right here by your side, okay?

154
00:10:05,603 --> 00:10:08,037
If she finds out I'm in this body,

155
00:10:08,037 --> 00:10:10,137
she'll follow me around

156
00:10:10,137 --> 00:10:14,970
24-7, day and night, around the clock.

157
00:10:33,770 --> 00:10:37,271
No matter what I tell her,

158
00:10:37,271 --> 00:10:41,503
she won't listen to me.

159
00:10:43,171 --> 00:10:47,371
You can't reason with her.

160
00:10:50,870 --> 00:10:52,670
Really?

161
00:10:52,670 --> 00:10:54,338
Then she shouldn't know.

162
00:10:54,338 --> 00:10:55,570
Let's go.

163
00:10:56,503 --> 00:10:58,570
So there was someone who
was willing to take Gyeong Jun.

164
00:10:58,570 --> 00:11:00,137
I know.

165
00:11:00,137 --> 00:11:03,004
We'd need his doctor's authorization
to put him on a plane, right?

166
00:11:03,004 --> 00:11:05,637
If the doctor's still around,

167
00:11:05,637 --> 00:11:06,970
we could get Gyeong Jun
discharged tonight, right?

168
00:11:06,970 --> 00:11:09,603
I'm sure there are morning flights to L.A.

169
00:11:13,237 --> 00:11:16,737
He's in a good mood. He must have
decided to send me to the States.

170
00:11:16,737 --> 00:11:17,970
What should we do?

171
00:11:17,970 --> 00:11:21,937
How will we talk her out of it?
She already has your uncle's permission.

172
00:11:21,937 --> 00:11:24,037
Like I said, you can't reason with her.

173
00:11:24,037 --> 00:11:28,071
We need to shock her
and take her down by surprise.

174
00:11:36,371 --> 00:11:39,904
It seems like you're just sleeping.

175
00:11:40,470 --> 00:11:43,470
In fairy tales,

176
00:11:43,470 --> 00:11:48,570
the princess awakens when
she is kissed by Prince Charming.

177
00:12:09,004 --> 00:12:12,637
I told you to go home, and yet here you are.

178
00:12:14,037 --> 00:12:17,670
Thank goodness I found out.

179
00:12:20,804 --> 00:12:22,770
Mister,

180
00:12:22,770 --> 00:12:25,171
why did you lie to me?

181
00:12:25,171 --> 00:12:27,670
You're a liar, a quack, and a fraud.

182
00:12:27,670 --> 00:12:31,104
I'll tell the hospital you lied
about your patient.

183
00:12:31,104 --> 00:12:32,837
I never lied.

184
00:12:32,837 --> 00:12:36,171
As you can see, he is being
well taken care of here.

185
00:12:36,171 --> 00:12:38,870
I'm taking Gyeong Jun to the States.

186
00:12:38,870 --> 00:12:40,904
I bet that's what he'd want, too

187
00:12:40,904 --> 00:12:43,537
because no one here cares about him.

188
00:12:43,537 --> 00:12:45,670
I bet he'd want to stay here

189
00:12:45,670 --> 00:12:49,271
because the woman Gyeong Jun likes
is here in Korea.

190
00:12:49,271 --> 00:12:50,537
Someone he likes?

191
00:12:50,537 --> 00:12:51,537
But Gyeong Jun's not interested in anyone.

192
00:12:51,537 --> 00:12:52,837
Oh, yes he is.

193
00:12:52,837 --> 00:12:53,837
She's right here.

194
00:12:57,570 --> 00:12:58,670
Ms. Gil.

195
00:12:58,670 --> 00:13:01,837
Gyeong Jun likes Ms. Gil Da Ran.

196
00:13:01,837 --> 00:13:04,670
Gyeong Jun

197
00:13:04,670 --> 00:13:07,037
likes her?

198
00:13:08,037 --> 00:13:11,737
Gyeong Jun likes me?

199
00:13:12,503 --> 00:13:14,071
Sure.

200
00:13:14,071 --> 00:13:18,237
He fell for her the moment he saw her
on the bus, so he got off with her.

201
00:13:18,237 --> 00:13:19,870
Really?

202
00:13:19,870 --> 00:13:21,470
He did get off the bus with me, but...

203
00:13:21,470 --> 00:13:22,937
He then followed you around

204
00:13:22,937 --> 00:13:25,970
and pretended to have accidentally
run into her at the furniture store.

205
00:13:26,970 --> 00:13:28,438
That's not true, right?

206
00:13:28,438 --> 00:13:34,371
We did run into each other
at a furniture store, but...

207
00:13:34,937 --> 00:13:36,603
No way.

208
00:13:37,204 --> 00:13:40,404
Gyeong Jun's not the type to follow
someone around like a stalker.

209
00:13:41,704 --> 00:13:45,137
I caught him following

210
00:13:45,137 --> 00:13:46,570
my fiancee around.

211
00:13:46,570 --> 00:13:48,438
I met with him to talk some sense to him

212
00:13:48,438 --> 00:13:51,338
when he told me this and that about his life.

213
00:13:51,338 --> 00:13:53,004
You're lying.

214
00:13:53,004 --> 00:13:54,037
No way.

215
00:13:54,037 --> 00:13:57,570
Then how else would I know
so much about him?

216
00:13:57,570 --> 00:14:03,670
As you said, I'm not the type
he'd normally befriend.

217
00:14:05,104 --> 00:14:08,371
But she's not the type
Gyeong Jun would like, either.

218
00:14:09,470 --> 00:14:13,837
He said he liked women who were
charismatic like Angelina Jolie,

219
00:14:13,837 --> 00:14:17,637
so I've been trying so hard
to work on my charisma.

220
00:14:22,304 --> 00:14:25,171
She's anything but charismatic.
He can't possibly like her.

221
00:14:25,737 --> 00:14:27,670
But she's pretty.

222
00:14:28,338 --> 00:14:30,870
He said she grew on him
because she was so pretty.

223
00:14:38,004 --> 00:14:41,004
So the one Gyeong Jun needs isn't you.

224
00:14:41,004 --> 00:14:43,737
It's her.

225
00:14:50,470 --> 00:14:52,603
Your name's Mary, right?

226
00:14:52,603 --> 00:14:55,937
I'll take good care of Gyeong Jun.

227
00:14:55,937 --> 00:15:01,404
I'm his teacher after all.

228
00:15:23,204 --> 00:15:25,503
She loses.

229
00:15:25,503 --> 00:15:27,204
Game over.

230
00:15:27,537 --> 00:15:29,037
Go, go!

231
00:15:32,904 --> 00:15:37,104
It must have been a real shocker to her
that you like someone else.

232
00:15:37,104 --> 00:15:40,503
Once I return to my body,
I can explain to her.

233
00:15:41,071 --> 00:15:43,204
What you said isn't true, right?

234
00:15:43,204 --> 00:15:47,204
You made up that whole thing
about how you like me, right?

235
00:15:49,737 --> 00:15:51,438
But of course.

236
00:15:51,438 --> 00:15:54,404
Don't tell me you were worried.

237
00:15:54,404 --> 00:15:56,304
Talk about delusional.

238
00:15:56,304 --> 00:15:57,870
All you had to say was that it wasn't true.

239
00:15:57,870 --> 00:16:00,404
Mind your manners.

240
00:16:00,404 --> 00:16:01,503
Yes, ma'am.

241
00:16:02,171 --> 00:16:04,837
You tend to flatter yourself, Ms. Gil.

242
00:16:08,438 --> 00:16:10,271
Why did he have to say he found me pretty?

243
00:16:10,271 --> 00:16:12,071
That's what Yun Jae said.

244
00:16:20,737 --> 00:16:22,570
I should have known.

245
00:16:23,204 --> 00:16:27,237
You're not the type to take pictures
of someone you don't care for.

246
00:16:32,770 --> 00:16:34,870
We got her good. You saw, right?

247
00:16:34,870 --> 00:16:36,438
I must be a genius.

248
00:16:36,438 --> 00:16:38,137
I'm so proud of myself.

249
00:16:39,104 --> 00:16:41,037
But you don't feel the same way, right?

250
00:16:42,304 --> 00:16:45,237
You don't like Gyeong Jun, right?

251
00:16:45,237 --> 00:16:46,204
No.

252
00:16:46,204 --> 00:16:49,570
I'm about to marry Yun Jae.

253
00:16:49,570 --> 00:16:51,004
Be that as it may,

254
00:16:51,004 --> 00:16:55,037
Gyeong Jun's much hotter than him.

255
00:16:56,071 --> 00:16:58,171
That's not true.

256
00:16:58,171 --> 00:17:04,637
In my eyes, Gyeong Jun's just a kid
who doesn't know better.

257
00:17:04,637 --> 00:17:08,770
I'm not the type who'd play
childish games with my students.

258
00:17:08,770 --> 00:17:10,104
Were you worried?

259
00:17:10,104 --> 00:17:14,004
Talk about delusional.

260
00:17:14,004 --> 00:17:17,371
You can never ever change your mind.

261
00:17:17,371 --> 00:17:19,171
That will never ever happen.

262
00:17:19,171 --> 00:17:22,670
You seem like a good person.
